The Tidemouth Dunes zone where Reach Warden and Mafdet Harbor Warden jurisdictions overlap has been infiltrated by hostile elements exploiting the gap in authority. Tidemouth raiders, rogue Outriders who have broken from the Red Sand Accounts, and jurisdiction specters are disrupting enforcement actions in the transition zone. The Mafdet postmaster requires the zone cleared before the formal jurisdictional boundary review can proceed.
The hostile elements in the Tidemouth jurisdiction overlap zone have been eliminated. The Tidemouth Dunes are accessible for the formal boundary review between Reach Warden and Mafdet Harbor Warden authority. The postmaster has submitted an enforcement sweep report to the Mafdet Harbor Authority as documentation supporting the proposed joint-jurisdiction compact.

